{"cursor":"25225","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n\n\nAn 'envelope' is a common packaging item, usually made of thin flat material. It\nis designed to contain a flat object, such as a letter or card.\n\nTraditional envelopes are made from sheets of paper cut to one of three shapes:\na rhombus, a short-arm cross, or a kite. These shapes allow for the creation of\nthe envelope structure by folding the sheet sides around a central rectangular\narea. In this manner, a rectangle-faced enclosure is formed with an arrangement\nof four flaps on the reverse side.\n","linknr":440,"url":"Envelope","recorded":1362563016,"links":81,"instances":["philately","archaeologist","postal_reformer","message","united_kingdom"],"pdf":["http://www.postalmuseum.si.edu/industrywhitepapers/EMA_History.pdf","http://www.postalmuseum.si.edu/industrywhitepapers/EMA_History.pdf"],"categories":["Envelopes|","Postal system","Stationery","Paper products","Postal history","Packaging","Domestic implements"],"headings":["Overview","Manufacture","Mailers","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Envelope_-_Boonville_Address-000.jpg/220px-Envelope_-_Boonville_Address-000.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Envelope_-_Boonville_Address-002.jpg/220px-Envelope_-_Boonville_Address-002.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Envelope_-_Wood_Food_Company-000.jpg/220px-Envelope_-_Wood_Food_Company-000.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/USPatent701839-CallahanAmericus-WindowedEnvelope.gif/220px-USPatent701839-CallahanAmericus-WindowedEnv